# Solution: javascript_ml_nlp_expert_053_architectural_understanding_expert_01

## Key Files Identified

- /app/project/src/module_14.js - WindowedSentimentAggregator: Listens to sentiment-prediction events, performs sliding-window aggregation per community, and republishes aggregates
- /app/project/src/module_38.js - Real-Time Fairness & Drift Monitor: Listens to prediction events, maintains sliding-window cache, computes fairness metrics (statistical parity, equal opportunity) and drift statistics (PSI)
- /app/project/src/module_46.js - Real-Time Concept-Drift Monitor: Computes sliding-window statistics and fires `model.retrain.requested` events when KL-divergence threshold is exceeded
- /app/project/src/module_50.js - Metric Monitor & Anomaly Publisher: Queries Prometheus for model-serving metrics, detects anomalies, and publishes to Kafka
- /app/project/src/module_60.js - ModelPerformanceMonitor: Subscribes to model-serving metrics stream, calculates rolling statistics, detects drift/threshold violations
- /app/project/src/module_21.js - FeatureEngineeringPipeline: Domain-event ingestion and real-time feature-engineering pipeline
- /app/project/src/module_2.js - High-throughput micro-pipeline: Raw social signals → feature engineering → model invocation → enriched insights
- /app/project/src/config.js - Centralized configuration module with Kafka, PostgreSQL, Redis, MLflow, and observability settings
- /app/project/src/constants.js - Global constants including pipeline stage identifiers (INGESTION, FEATURE_ENGINEERING, INFERENCE, POST_PROCESSING, MONITORING)

## Code Evidence

### Pipeline Stage Identifiers (module constants.js)
```javascript
// File: /app/project/src/constants.js
// Lines: 125-131
export const PipelineStage = deepFreeze({
  INGESTION: 'ingestion',
  FEATURE_ENGINEERING: 'feature_engineering',
  INFERENCE: 'inference',
  POST_PROCESSING: 'post_processing',
  MONITORING: 'monitoring',
});
```

### Module 14 - WindowedSentimentAggregator (Kafka consumer/producer with JSON serialization)
